title: Grateful Dead Live at Deer Creek Music Center on 1992-06-28
description: Help On The Way-> Slipknot!-> Franklin's Tower, Wang Dang Doodle, Just Like Tom Thumb's Blues, To Lay Me Down, El Paso, New Speedway Boogie-> Smokestack Lightning China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider-> Estimated Prophet, Way To Go Home-> Drums-> Jam-> The Last Time-> China Doll-> Around & Around, E: Casey Jones

reviews.review_text: This show rocks I belive this one of the first times Casey Jones was played in a in a long time and I was backstage with my good friend Seth!!! I you ever read this you know who you are!!!!!!!!!!

Close but not quite Wasnt the first time, it was the second, but it still was looooooooose and fun - scorching bright white lights behind Billy and his Train horns........Just like a headlight on a northbound train.
Solid For late in the game - there are some really nice peaks to this. There are some minor issues with the sound.

I almost died To Lay Me Down had me in a pool of sweat that only my silly friend and an even sillier El Paso got me out of.

Not sure what the heck was going on but if this song takes you places then this version should do it.  Over all a very average show made better by the fact it was Deer Creek.
